The Kwara State government has monetised the COVID-19 palliatives for the people of Kaiama in the northern axis of the state because of the area’s difficult terrain. The government’s decision, it was gathered, was in response to the request of the political leaders in the area, regarded as the food basket of the state. One of the political leaders and commissioner for Environment, Aliyu Muhammad Saifudeen, confirmed the state government’s gesture to LEADERSHIP, yesterday. While thanking Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq for acceding to their request, Saifudeen said: “The entire people of Kaiama local government area felt the impact of the palliatives which was monetised by the government in response to the request by their political leaders as the best option for their peculiarity as farmers and in view of the difficult terrain of the area in terms of mobility.”  